reviews.text: If you don't want to miss your train, get there on time and make sure that you choose the right carrige(not too full) so ou can get a seat and you are not cramped. Otherwise the station coffee place is a buisness run by two very sweet husband and wife. The staff are always very friendly and the station staff are too!
Aside from the problematic train services running to and from this station, I've had issues with the faulty card readers not updating my journey and costing me more than they should

Horrendous service. I'm constantly late for work or having to get cabs because of the weekly if not daily delayed or cancelled trains-which on the national rail ap show they're on time until about two minutes prior to "arriving" at the station. 
Still, at least I'm paying £1,600 a year for the privilege of a terrible service, never getting a seat and sweating like a pig in summer as these trains don't have air con. 🍾
